content:
You can use Financial Account and related objects without installing the Financial Services Cloud managed package. These standard objects provide greater control and flexibility over your data models, enabling seamless integration.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions.

Enable the Financial Account Management Standard Objects setting to access these standard objects. If you're currently using objects from the Financial Services Cloud Managed package, plan metadata and data migration before switching.

You can model financial accounts by using a set of standard objects, such as Financial Account, Financial Account Party, and Financial Account Transaction.

Consider planning your transition if you're switching from the managed package to these standard objects. Plan ahead for user teams, partners, and clients.

Enable the setting by going to Setup > Financial Services Cloud > Enable Financial Account Management Standard Objects.
Assign permissions for users to access the Financial Account and related standard objects by assigning permission sets.
Considerations include planning metadata and data migration, and avoiding mixing managed package and standard objects when setting up financial accounts and their features.
title: Configuring Financial Account Management in Salesforce
